Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It showcases a real-life track enthusiast and her father, and aims to show how the Gemini app can provide a starting point, thought starter, or early draft for someone looking for ideas for their writing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2199, \"end\": 2205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9995308496547646, \"rank\": 0.0004693705505511099, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Dear Sydney\\\" ad does indicate that the fan letter Gemini AI produces based on the dad's prompt is meant to be \\\"a draft to get you started,\\\" per an image displayed on-screen.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9995308496547646, \"rank\": 0.0004693705505511099, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.993452123899206, \"rank\": 0.006591033051776018, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The kerfuffle comes after Apple - typically considered a gold standard of marketing savvy - evoked a similar backlash over its \\\"Crush!\\\"\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.650043495426439e-1